title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom AR 15
postcontent: I have for sale or trade a custom ar15. I built it piece by piece. I used a jse complete upper 20 inch stainless steel bull barrel with a 1/8 inch rate of twist chambered in .223 wylde. It has an aluminum rifle length free float tube. The lower I built from an R guns stripped lower with a DPMS lower parts kit and an ATI Strikeforce collapsible stock wrapped around a commercial buffer tube. It has an accuwedge between the upper and lower receivers to take all of the play out of it, and also includes a Mako magazine well grip. Included in this package are 3-20 round GI mags and 1-20 round p-mag. It is all topped of with a Nikon Prostaff 3-9x40mm scope with a BDC reticle. This reticle is very useful because you can log on to the www.nikonhunting.com and launch their spot on application that lets you choose the make and weight of your ammunition and it will tell you exactly where your bullet will hit at each range for any wind and temperature situation.  Also included are 20 rounds of 75 grain ultramax match hollow point .223 ammunition that are great for hunting and also very accurate (the rounds I used to shoot the grouping in the picture). Also included are 320 rounds of American Eagle Rifle Ammo .223 REM 55GR.FMJ that are due to arrive by mail tomorrow. This is a very nice rifle that I am very proud of. The reason I am getting rid of it is that due to the current political climate their value has increased so much that I cannot pass this up. I got engaged approximately two weeks ago so money has suddenly become a big issue, or I would be holding on to this weapon. The listed price is somewhat negotiable. By the way, the grouping in the picture was shot from approximately 50 yards with 8 shots. The one bullet hole that hit high and to the left of the bullseye next to the number 10 was the first cold bore shot. If that hole is not included in the grouping, then the next 7 shots formed a grouping approximately 7/16's of an inch wide from outside to outside. This would be 7/8's of an inch at a hundred yards, a sub moa grouping.

title: For Sale:  Colt National Match 45
postcontent: Colt Gold Cup National Match that remains in excellent original condition. This is a "Pre-Series 70" pistol, was made in 1966. The National Match is the competition/target version of the famous 1911/Government Model line. Chambered for the .45 ACP it had some features that were unique at the time. These features included the flat top slide with angled cocking serrations, Elliason adjustable rear sight, specially fitted barrel bushing, NM barrel, conical recoil spring plug, special trigger, etc. This pistol is in excellent overall condition. There are a few light handling marks scattered about, but no rust or pitting. I'd grade the original blue finish at about 95-97%. The original checkered walnut grips feature gold Colt medallions and are in excellent shape without cracks, chips or significant wear. The pistol is in perfect working order and the bore is excellent. This fine pistol comes in an original National Match box, target and instruction sheet.  The last of the old style Pre-Series 70 National Match pistols was manufactured in 1970 at serial number 37025-NM.  I am asking $2000.00.
